elements.title: Play_Header
elements.longDescription: Challenge other players or Unreal Tournament’s legendary AI opponents in fast, skill-based competition. This reimagining of the classic first person shooter is being developed by Epic Games with the help of the community.

elements.title: Polaris
elements.longDescription: Liandri's deep space mining exploration station Polaris is an ideal location for high level capture the flag tournaments.

elements.title: Backspace
elements.longDescription: The ancient winds that permeate this bloodthirsty conclave are said to echo the calls of the old protectors, summoning exiled warriors from afar to prove their worth in trials of combat.

elements.title: Salt
elements.longDescription: This monastery/fortress was once home to an ancient order of monks dedicated to contemplating the afterlife. Liandri acquired the site via their ‘Heritage Program’ under the express understanding that they continued the orders work; unfortunately for the monks nobody specified how.

elements.title: Unsaved
elements.longDescription: Constructed to exploit a large deposit of Tarydium in the core of a small moon, this remote satellite mining facility is one of the newer Tournament Arenas offered by LMC. Due to the presence of the three X29 fusion devices, the moon has now been displaced into a decaying orbit. This has led its former crew to designate the facility … Unsaved.

elements.title: Batrankus
elements.longDescription: Once main hub of an ancient water distribution system, this site is now completely adapted for the Tournament. Happy Fragging!

elements.title: Omega Armor
elements.longDescription: Viper awesomeness

elements.title: Pistola
elements.description: Remake of a classic Capture the Flag map from community developer Yemi Ajayi
elements.longDescription:
Pistola is a symmetrical CTF map suited for 8 players. This version is from Yemi Ajayi and represents a community driven remake of a classic Unreal Tournament Map.

During the Skaarj Wars, the Liandri corporation built extensive bunker systems through the hollows of the Pistola Mountain Range in an attempt to secure key assets and provide safe avenues for the transport of wartime infrastructure. The facilities were decommissioned after the Seven Day Siege, and lay empty for decades until they were refurbished as a rusty and decayed Tournament arena. The Pistola bunkers proved to be so popular, however, that the Liandri corp has decided to invest in a complete overhaul to support this year's Tournament.

elements.title: Cardboard Box
elements.description: It's a box, made of cardboard.
elements.longDescription: This box made of paper won't protect your head very well, but it will hide the shame of your last-place finish. It also changes its face depending on how well you are doing.

elements.title: The Money Hat
elements.description: The prize pool gets bigger with every purchase.
elements.longDescription: This cap is for the player who starts incognito but flips that brim around when it's go time. At first it's just a cap, but when you tie or take the lead it turns to gold. Epic is putting 100 percent of the proceeds from this hat into the prize pool for the first competitive season of Unreal Tournament.

elements.title: Unreal Helmet
elements.longDescription: We all know gibs are messy. Post-match cleanup costs continue to rise year-over-year. With the new Unreal Helmet save yourself from the mess of a match with this full eye protection and helmet. In normal play it is just a helmet. As soon as you tie or take the lead in any game, the gold Unreal Tournament symbol appears on your helmet and your goggles glow gold.

elements.title: Skull Mask
elements.longDescription: Is terrorizing the enemy your cup of tea? This cosmetic item covers your face, giving it a more sinister look. In normal play it is your usual skull mask of doom. As soon as you take or tie the lead in any game, the mask grows horns to show everybody who is dominant.

elements.title: Lea Observatory
elements.description: A new Deathmatch level from community developer Neil Moore.
elements.longDescription:
Lea is a Deathmatch map that is ideally suited for 2-to-4 players. Its compact layout and use of advanced movement systems make for competitive Duel matches and intense Deathmatch gameplay. This map is based on a design by Cédric "HTK" Mourouvin.

 Located in the constellation Lyra, about 1,200 light years from Earth and orbiting Kepler-62, lies the blue gem known as Lea. Though tropical storms often rage on the surface, interesting aquatic life has been discovered in the depths of Lea's oceans. Pure Labs, backed by funding from the Liandri Corporation, built this deep sea observatory that doubles as an Arena for the Grand Tournament.
